The AR-57 is a carbine/personal defense weapon designed and produced by AR57 LLC of Kent, Washington in the United States. It is available as either an upper receiver package for the AR-15/M16 rifle or as a complete rifle. Versions are offered in both semi-auto only and in select fire, and was marketed primarily to law enforcement agencies as a potential competitor to the FN P90.

While the AR-57 shares many outward similarities to the AR-15, there are a number of key differences. Unlike a standard AR-15, which uses a direct impingement system to work the action, the AR-57 instead cycles via conventional direct blowback in much the same way a submachine gun might. Where the differences become most apparent is with the ammunition. The AR-57 is chambered for the 5.7×28mm round developed by Belgian firearms manufacturer FN Herstal, and feeds from standard FN P90 magazines. Also like the FN P90, the AR57 ejects spent brass downwards, with casings falling out through what would normally be the magazine well on a standard AR-15. It is possible to use a hollow magazine inserted into this mag well as a brass catcher.

items.name: Takehiko Inoue (Vagabond) - Artist Style (LoRA/Lycoris)
items.description:
If you enjoyed this model, why don't you check out my other works? I put a lot of effort into correctly recreating artist styles and making the occasional character LoRA.😊

This model was trained using the collab/guide by holostrawberry [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free - colabs | Stable Diffusion Other | Civitai

About the artist:

Takehiko Inoue is famous for writing the series Slam Dunk and Vagabond, creating highly detailed art with strong contrasts. This model was made using 79 images from the second series, Vagabond.

Weights & Prompts

The only necessary prompt is:

vagabond_style

To get the black and white manga style use

monochrome

I also recommend including "comic" in the negative prompts to prevent panels.

LoCon:

For the weights use 0.6-1.0, adjust to taste.

It is pretty strong and should be tuned to a lower weight when combined with other LoRA. Female characters in particular have a limited range at 1.0 weight.

LoRA:

For the weights I recommend 0.9-1. As it was trained exclusively on black and white pages including monochrome in the negative prompts can force colorized images.

When not otherwise specified it will tend to traditional clothes and building.

As usual I have included an XYZ plot to show how the weight affects the prompt. This version is pretty heavyweight so including the lora doesn't just change the style but massively affects the composition as well.

Please leave a review if you enjoyed this model or have problems with it. This helps me with improving future models and finetuning them in general. Give it a try and throw some images down below! 👇

items.name: Fantastic West
items.description:
Welcome to the Fantastic West! Keep your hands and arms inside the covered wagon and remember not to pet the rattlesnakes.

My favorite checkpoint to use this with is realisticVision but I've also had success with dreamshaper and deliberate. I trained it on different orientations but there were more landscape styles than portrait styles, so I recommend sticking to landscape orientation. The differences between this lora and most checkpoints becomes really striking with western towns. I've had lots of great luck with drawing old west towns. To trigger an old west town use the keywords western town or old west town. To trigger a landscape use western landscape. It's somewhat versatile with the scenery so play around with different ideas. I added the trigger fantwest to just trigger the lora in general, but I don't always have to use it to get it to influence the style.

I use this at 1.0 weight, though you may want to go up or down depending on the effect you're going for. I also have had good luck with CFG between 5 and 7, but CFG doesn't seem to really change this one much, i'm not sure why. Also, I use clip skip 1, so if you have it set to 2 for all your waifus, you might want to dial it back down to 1 for your old west scenery.

I trained this lora on a bunch of images depicting old western towns, landscapes, animals, etc. It's not particularly good at drawing animals since that isn't what it was intended for, but it's fairly easy to add them into the landscape. I added pictures of animals (horses, cows, coyotes, etc) to the training set to prevent it from training animals out out the lora, not to get high detailed animals. Please don't downrate this lora if it can't draw animals, that's not the intent of this lora. I also didn't train it on humans or cowboys, since that should be the topic of a different lora.

items.name: WW1 - French Soldier uniform
items.description:
WW1 - French Soldier uniform


How to use

This model has been trained on base SD 1.5. It should be compatible with almost any checkpoint although quality may vary. It works with male or female characters. There is no keyword to invoke but I personally use "WW1 French soldier, a man". The LoRA weight depends heavily on what you want to do so it's hard to recommend something specific, I would say from 0.5 to 0.9 give the best results in normal scenarios.

Historical accuracy

This LoRA imitates the common uniform of French soldiers during WW1 from around 1915 and up to the end of the war (Bleu Horizon). It does not feature the uniform from the start of the war (red pants, cap, no helmet).

Dataset

Only images of costumes or reenactments were used because it was far easier than using original images which are mostly black and white and in bad quality. An alternative would have been to use images from WW1 movies, but costumes were faster to acquire, as only 16 images were needed.

I plan to make other LoRA themed about World War 1 so don't hesitate to give advice and feedback!

items.name: 【Character / Art Style】Bad Girl
items.description:
2023/6/17 update

Fix the problem of poor image quality generated by using WD VAE. The preview images are generated using 1.6 version, 2.0 version Yesmix and MeinaMix to verify the compatibility of this LoRA model on different base models.

2023/5/29 update

Update dataset. New version is trained using new craft.

Introduction

The original intention of creating the Fashion Girl model was to generate fashionable anime girl images (2.5d girl images). The idea of creating a new model emerged in order to generate more rebellious and cooler girl images. Therefore, this LoRA model can be used to generate cooler and naughtier girl images compared to the Fashion Girl model. The trigger tag is 'bad-girl'. The 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) are recommended. 0.6 ~ 0.8 weights are good. The preview images are generated using 1.6 version (original) YesMix.

This model will be continuously updated as the dataset is updated (although images that satisfy the conditions are not much).

Cautions (Must Read)

For anime model,

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

  • Some preview images are generated using 'Hires Fix' and upscaled using 'SD Upscale'. Thus, if you wanna generate the preview images, pls download the original preview images and analyze them using 'PNG INFO' in webui to get all generating information.

BTW, make sure set this option in 'Stable Diffusion' settings to 'CPU' to successfully regenerate the preview images with the same seed.

  • The training resolution of this model is 1024x1024, so generating resolution must not exceed this range. Try to use 'hires fix' to prevent this problem and help to generate higher-resolution images.

  • For 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) users, make sure add '--no-half-vae' in command line of webui to prevent generating black images. See voldy's log for the details of edit method. For high-performance GPU, make sure 'medvram' and 'lowvram' mode are disabled.

A commission of @findingavarice521.

Lyna Pérez (aka Lynaritaa) is an American model and social media celebrity with around 10M followers on Instagram.

This is a 1000-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images with my usual settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (lynaritaa:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, long brown coat, ((turtleneck sweater:1.2), trousers, long haircut, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6"

items.name: Age Slider
items.description:
Update June 13th adding updated Young Versions... V2

I developed this age slider to work with my Children's Stories model. Some Stable Diffusion models have difficulty generating younger people. This embedding will fix that for you. It can make anyone, in any Lora, on any model, younger. Even animals and fantasy creatures.

Follow me to make sure you see new styles, poses and Nobodys when I post them. Things move fast on this site, it's easy to miss.

How to use:
Just use one of the positive prompts listed to get the desired results. Use them at strength of 1. That means to put them at the beginning of your prompt or make sure they have the appropriate modifier brackets. Example, for automatic1111 it would be (AS-YoungerV2) or (AS-YoungerV2:1.0), the parenthesis are required. They are stackable, so you can combine them together to help with stubborn models. A negative embedding is also included for extra brute force if needed. There are 4 files to download for younger, and 4 for older, check the version tabs at the top.

These embeddings make people/creatures/characters younger.

  • AS-YoungV2-Neg: Place in your negative prompt at strength of 1.0 to 1.3, generally removes adults from the scene.

  • AS-YoungV2: Place at the beginning of your positive prompt at strength of 1.0 to 1.3. Conceptually teenager, may vary by model, lora, or prompts.

  • AS-YoungerV2: Place at the beginning of your positive prompt at strength of 1.0 to 1.3. Conceptually child, may vary by model, lora, or prompts.

  • AS-YoungestV2: Place at the beginning of your positive prompt at strength of 1.0 to 1.3. Conceptually toddler/baby, may vary by model, lora, or prompts

These embeddings make people/creatures/characters adult or older.

  • AS-Adult-Neg: Place in your negative prompt at strength of 1.0 to 1.3. This will remove any young people and/or youth from the scene.

  • AS-Adult: Place at the beginning of your positive prompt at strength of 1.0 to 1.3. Conceptually fully matured adult 20s to 30s, may vary by model, lora, or prompts.

  • AS-MidAged: Place at the beginning of your positive prompt at strength of 1.0 to 1.3. Conceptually middle-aged adult 40s to 60s, may vary by model, lora, or prompts.

  • AS-Elderly: Place at the beginning of your positive prompt at strength of 1.0 to 1.3. Conceptually elderly adult 70s +, may vary by model, lora, or prompts.

These are the concepts for the embeddings. Some models, character LoRAs, or embeddings might be too rigid, so increase strength or stack on multiple to get the desired result. Additional prompts may help as well.

Do you have requests? I've been putting in many more hours lately with this. That's my problem, not yours. But if you'd like to tip me, buy me a beer. Beer encourages me to ignore work and make AI models instead. Tip and make a request. I'll give it a shot if I can. Here at Ko-Fi

items.name: MIO
items.description:
On my other LoRA's I've stated that I like them to be able to handle more than 1 character. That got me to wondering what else was possible. I often use HiPoly in my renders, sometimes one of the MANY different breast size / body proportions LoRA's, then maybe a character LoRA (similar to the Nobody series from Zovya) also. Then comes the hassle of finding the right weights of each one to generate an image that's not plagued with fractals/artifacts and still produces the desired result.

My answer to this problem was fairly simple really, it just took some time to accomplish. Generate a LOT of images the way I want them, and make a LoRA out of it. 380 renders of 19 different girls and 133 renders of 7 different breast sizes later I've com up with MIO. (many-in-one) About 99% of the training images were created using Lyriel so it will work quite well with it. It has been "baked" slightly more than I prefer but that was because of the way I accomplished the end result. The characters and breasts were trained separately creating a LoRA for each that was a little heavier than I like (about 40% more) then merged 50-50 in Kohya_ss.

As I said, there's 19 girls in all and each is slightly different even if sometimes their faces tend to be similar. Most have a clear nationality that comes through in renders even without prompting such as Cheyenne (Native American), Lupita (Latina), Priya (Indian), what I mean by this is that quite often Cheyenne has deerskin clothes, if you put a dress on Lupita it likes to look like a quinceanera gown, and Priya leans towards a sari.

On the breast sizing side of things, the basic prompts with an underscore are the correct ones, but to add more precision and get the results as I intended them you should use them in conjunction with helpers. IE when I prompt (flat chest) I'm usually meaning just that, but most checkpoints and breast sizing LoRAs will actually give you what I consider small breasts with that prompt. To fix that just combine (flat_chest) with (no bewbs). Small, medium, and large are pretty straight forward. Huge, giga, and crazy used alone often look almost similar but the intention is for huge to be just that, huge naturals. Giga is more of a huge fake breast, and crazy is well, crazy. The fix is to prompt as (big giga_breasts) and (gigantic crazy_breasts) just be prepared to negative prompt big/wide/thick hips, unless that's what you want.

Please like and review. post your creations with it. I love seeing what people make more that seeing the downloads go up.

The only thing I ask is to please prompt responsibly. This Lora is geared towards anime/semi-realism and because of what it combines together it REALLY likes to create NSFW images but typically SFW in the positive and NSFW in the negative helps to greatly reduce this to near none.

Fun side note Tuya was not actually trained as a furry but because of the hairstyle she had in her training images the end result is a girl that often has dog/wolf ears. if you increase the LoRA weight over 1 and add furry to a prompt with her name you can have some fun with it.

modelVersions.name: RevisedBasics
modelVersions.description:
While making Millennium Girls I learned a few new things and wanted to revisit MIO. This version I have removed the extra girls added with BAB, I've removed the breast and butt training. This version has training on only the 19 girls originally included with MIO. Later I will make a standalone version of BAB (butts and boobs) or perhaps I will separate them.

The reason for this change is that as MIO evolved in the previous versions it became harder and harder to render each girl the way they were intended to look. There had to be more tags included to get the right hair, skin tone, body, etc. This version now has only two purposes, to be a girlpack, and a render enhancer. (For some reason Jun still needs the white hair prompt and Nadia still needs short blonde hair) but all others work much better.

The last image is an example of how well it will work to add detail with fewer prompts. The Kate Beckinsale image uses none of the triggers for the LoRA and has no positive quality prompts.

modelVersions.name: v2.0 - MIOandBaBs
trainedWords: All other prompts included in MIO
modelVersions.description: Originally when I made MIO, the intention was to include butt sizing also. The problem I ran into was that it was difficult to prompt for it and get consistent results that could be used for training data. I still wanted the results to be original data and preferably AI but perhaps there was a compromise. Enter VAM. This version is no longer trained on 100% AI generated material, but the supplementary images were created in VAM and it now includes 4 different butt sizing prompts and 5 more girls for a total of 24 original girls. Including the new prompts for derrieres will cause the LORA to focus heavily on that part of the body and it still has trouble making them truly small, but it does add another layer of control to generations. This new version has lost some of the breast control it once had, but I find it still usable for that and as a result of the included VAM rendered girls the original MIO girls have a slightly softer body type instead of the rippling muscles that were common before.
